Monsoon rains and snowmelt have left 200,000 people stranded in northern Bangladesh, where annual floods are a common occurrence.
The Brahmaputra river is overflowing, posing a serious threat.
The death toll in India, Bangladesh, and Nepal has surpassed 100, with millions displaced.
Relief efforts are underway, with the government and military providing aid and evacuation services.
The situation is dire, with millions affected and thousands forced to seek refuge in relief centers.
International aid, including 2.5 million USD from the UK, is being channeled to support relief efforts in the worst-hit areas.
